New Agent Mode in Warp AI

Now you can write plain English on the command line and Agent Mode in Warp AI will guide you through any development task.

Watch a demo of Agent Mode in action ⏵ ( https://youtu.be/s5nSOiXeJ8g )

Unlike the old version of Warp AI that was confined to a chat panel, this new generation of Warp AI lives on the command line and it can make highly tailored recommendations based on your terminal session.

Agent Mode can:
* Interpret natural language in addition to traditional commands
* Learn any CLI with public docs or –help
*
Ask permission to execute commands to gather more context

Read the announcement blog ( https://www.warp.dev/blog/agent-mode?utm_source=annoucement&utm_medium=email&utm_campaign=agent_mode_launch ) to learn more or visit the example gallery ( https://www.warp.dev/ai?utm_source=annoucement&utm_medium=email&utm_campaign=agent_mode_launch ) for inspiration.

